\section{Cash Spending Use Case}
Here is the use case for our MyMoney application.

\medskip
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{| l | p{6cm} |}
\hline

Use Case ID  & MyMoneyW18COMP354a\\
\hline
Use Case Name  & Cash Spending\\
\hline
Goal/Purpose  & Allow a user to manage his/her cash spendings via a desktop application\\
\hline
Actors  & Any User\\
\hline
Pre-Conditions &  User has installed "My Money" desktop application \\
\hline
Post-Conditions & NA \\
\hline
Main Flow & User wants to update his/her incomes.
1. User opens the application and selects the Cash Spending button. 
2. The application displays two possible options for the user: incomes or outcomes
3. User enters the value of his income or outcome and presses the "done" button.
4. The application stores the value entered by the user and displays a message of success for the operation, including the value. Also, there are displayed two options for the user: make changes or go back to the front page
\\
\hline
Alternate Flow(s) & NA

\\
\hline
Exception Flow(s) & â€¢ 1. User entered invalid inputs(ex. a negative number)
   b) The application displays error message, and urges user to fix the input. \\
\hline

\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\end{document}
